      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah we checked the ALB timeouts and they seem fine. the connectivity seems solid for most of the day then it just randomly snaps. could it be an MTU mismatch or something like that? maybe something in the VPC peering? it's just so random it feels like it's happening for no reason at all.",
